{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":928,"text":"So, a few years ago I heard\nan interesting rumor."},{"time":4389,"text":"Apparently, the head\nof a large pet food company"},{"time":6801,"text":"would go into the annual\nshareholder's meeting"},{"time":9080,"text":"with can of dog food."},{"time":10565,"text":"And he would eat the can of dog food."},{"time":12690,"text":"And this was his way of convincing them\nthat if it was good enough for him,"},{"time":16267,"text":"it was good enough for their pets."},{"time":17968,"text":"This strategy is now known\nas \"dogfooding,\""},{"time":20428,"text":"and it's a common strategy\nin the business world."},{"time":22771,"text":"It doesn't mean everyone\ngoes in and eats dog food,"},{"time":25279,"text":"but businesspeople\nwill use their own products"},{"time":27524,"text":"to demonstrate that they feel --"},{"time":29085,"text":"that they're confident in them."},{"time":30814,"text":"Now, this is a widespread practice,"},{"time":32763,"text":"but I think what's really interesting\nis when you find exceptions"},{"time":35882,"text":"to this rule,"},{"time":37057,"text":"when you find cases of businesses\nor people in businesses"},{"time":39788,"text":"who don't use their own products."},{"time":41406,"text":"Turns out there's one industry\nwhere this happens in a common way,"},{"time":44551,"text":"in a pretty regular way,"},{"time":45735,"text":"and that is the screen-based\ntech industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48193,"text":"So, in 2010, Steve Jobs,\nwhen he was releasing the iPad,"},{"time":52611,"text":"described the iPad as a device\nthat was \"extraordinary.\""},{"time":56377,"text":"\"The best browsing experience\nyou've ever had;"},{"time":58941,"text":"way better than a laptop,\nway better than a smartphone."},{"time":61698,"text":"It's an incredible experience.\""},{"time":63249,"text":"A couple of months later,\nhe was approached by a journalist"},{"time":66058,"text":"from the New York Times,"},{"time":67238,"text":"and they had a long phone call."},{"time":68761,"text":"At the end of the call,"},{"time":69955,"text":"the journalist threw in a question\nthat seemed like a sort of softball."},{"time":73369,"text":"He said to him, \"Your kids\nmust love the iPad.\""},{"time":76803,"text":"There's an obvious answer to this,"},{"time":78456,"text":"but what Jobs said\nreally staggered the journalist."},{"time":81099,"text":"He was very surprised,"},{"time":82314,"text":"because he said, \"They haven't used it."},{"time":84913,"text":"We limit how much technology\nour kids use at home.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":87859,"text":"This is a very common thing\nin the tech world."},{"time":91746,"text":"In fact, there's a school\nquite near Silicon Valley"},{"time":94205,"text":"called the Waldorf School\nof the Peninsula,"},{"time":96502,"text":"and they don't introduce screens\nuntil the eighth grade."},{"time":99690,"text":"What's really interesting about the school"},{"time":101756,"text":"is that 75 percent\nof the kids who go there"},{"time":103829,"text":"have parents who are high-level\nSilicon Valley tech execs."},{"time":107342,"text":"So when I heard about this, I thought\nit was interesting and surprising,"},{"time":110881,"text":"and it pushed me to consider\nwhat screens were doing to me"},{"time":113937,"text":"and to my family and the people I loved,"},{"time":115918,"text":"and to people at large."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117204,"text":"So for the last five years,"},{"time":119150,"text":"as a professor of business and psychology,"},{"time":121207,"text":"I've been studying the effect\nof screens on our lives."},{"time":124889,"text":"And I want to start by just focusing\non how much time they take from us,"},{"time":128995,"text":"and then we can talk about\nwhat that time looks like."},{"time":131525,"text":"What I'm showing you here\nis the average 24-hour workday"},{"time":134216,"text":"at three different points in history:"},{"time":136578,"text":"2007 -- 10 years ago --"},{"time":138604,"text":"2015"},{"time":140087,"text":"and then data that I collected,\nactually, only last week."},{"time":143129,"text":"And a lot of things haven't changed"},{"time":144902,"text":"all that much."},{"time":147320,"text":"We sleep roughly seven-and-a-half\nto eight hours a day;"},{"time":150119,"text":"some people say that's declined slightly,\nbut it hasn't changed much."},{"time":153460,"text":"We work eight-and-a-half\nto nine hours a day."},{"time":156738,"text":"We engage in survival activities --"},{"time":158494,"text":"these are things like eating\nand bathing and looking after kids --"},{"time":161645,"text":"about three hours a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162825,"text":"That leaves this white space."},{"time":164377,"text":"That's our personal time."},{"time":166068,"text":"That space is incredibly important to us."},{"time":169294,"text":"That's the space where we do things\nthat make us individuals."},{"time":172192,"text":"That's where hobbies happen,\nwhere we have close relationships,"},{"time":175317,"text":"where we really think about our lives,\nwhere we get creative,"},{"time":178223,"text":"where we zoom back and try to work out"},{"time":180061,"text":"whether our lives have been meaningful."},{"time":181945,"text":"We get some of that from work as well,"},{"time":183797,"text":"but when people look back on their lives"},{"time":185736,"text":"and wonder what their lives have been like"},{"time":187764,"text":"at the end of their lives,"},{"time":189031,"text":"you look at the last things they say --"},{"time":190942,"text":"they are talking about those moments\nthat happen in that white personal space."},{"time":194667,"text":"So it's sacred; it's important to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196694,"text":"Now, what I'm going to do is show you"},{"time":198569,"text":"how much of that space\nis taken up by screens across time."},{"time":201845,"text":"In 2007,"},{"time":203194,"text":"this much."},{"time":204369,"text":"That was the year that Apple\nintroduced the first iPhone."},{"time":207373,"text":"Eight years later,"},{"time":209239,"text":"this much."},{"time":211318,"text":"Now, this much."},{"time":213131,"text":"That's how much time we spend\nof that free time in front of our screens."},{"time":216593,"text":"This yellow area, this thin sliver,\nis where the magic happens."},{"time":219920,"text":"That's where your humanity lives."},{"time":221526,"text":"And right now, it's in a very small box."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224243,"text":"So what do we do about this?"},{"time":225892,"text":"Well, the first question is:"},{"time":227273,"text":"What does that red space look like?"},{"time":229156,"text":"Now, of course, screens are miraculous"},{"time":231285,"text":"in a lot of ways."},{"time":232737,"text":"I live in New York,"},{"time":234018,"text":"a lot of my family lives in Australia,"},{"time":236040,"text":"and I have a one-year-old son."},{"time":237494,"text":"The way I've been able to introduce\nthem to him is with screens."},{"time":241416,"text":"I couldn't have done that\n15 or 20 years ago"},{"time":243530,"text":"in quite the same way."},{"time":244712,"text":"So there's a lot of good\nthat comes from them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246893,"text":"One thing you can do is ask yourself:"},{"time":248763,"text":"What goes on during that time?"},{"time":250870,"text":"How enriching are the apps\nthat we're using?"},{"time":253332,"text":"And some are enriching."},{"time":254630,"text":"If you stop people while\nthey're using them and say,"},{"time":257096,"text":"\"Tell us how you feel right now,\""},{"time":258708,"text":"they say they feel pretty good\nabout these apps --"},{"time":261128,"text":"those that focus on relaxation,\nexercise, weather, reading,"},{"time":264512,"text":"education and health."},{"time":266079,"text":"They spend an average of nine\nminutes a day on each of these."},{"time":269237,"text":"These apps make them much less happy."},{"time":272099,"text":"About half the people, when you interrupt\nthem and say, \"How do you feel?\""},{"time":275727,"text":"say they don't feel good about using them."},{"time":277859,"text":"What's interesting about these --"},{"time":279514,"text":"dating, social networking, gaming,"},{"time":281248,"text":"entertainment, news, web browsing --"},{"time":283998,"text":"people spend 27 minutes a day\non each of these."},{"time":286628,"text":"We're spending three times longer\non the apps that don't make us happy."},{"time":290204,"text":"That doesn't seem very wise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292886,"text":"One of the reasons we spend\nso much time on these apps"},{"time":295448,"text":"that make us unhappy"},{"time":296624,"text":"is they rob us of stopping cues."},{"time":298180,"text":"Stopping cues were everywhere\nin the 20th century."},{"time":300583,"text":"They were baked into everything we did."},{"time":302471,"text":"A stopping cue is basically a signal\nthat it's time to move on,"},{"time":305911,"text":"to do something new,\nto do something different."},{"time":308632,"text":"And -- think about newspapers;\neventually you get to the end,"},{"time":311852,"text":"you fold the newspaper away,\nyou put it aside."},{"time":314173,"text":"The same with magazines, books --\nyou get to the end of a chapter,"},{"time":317355,"text":"prompts you to consider\nwhether you want to continue."},{"time":320504,"text":"You watched a show on TV,\neventually the show would end,"},{"time":323226,"text":"and then you'd have a week\nuntil the next one came."},{"time":325655,"text":"There were stopping cues everywhere."},{"time":327433,"text":"But the way we consume media today\nis such that there are no stopping cues."},{"time":331923,"text":"The news feed just rolls on,"},{"time":333522,"text":"and everything's bottomless:\nTwitter, Facebook, Instagram,"},{"time":337219,"text":"email, text messaging, the news."},{"time":340385,"text":"And when you do check\nall sorts of other sources,"},{"time":343379,"text":"you can just keep going on and on and on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345744,"text":"So, we can get a cue about what to do\nfrom Western Europe,"},{"time":350178,"text":"where they seem to have a number\nof pretty good ideas in the workplace."},{"time":353603,"text":"Here's one example.\nThis is a Dutch design firm."},{"time":356035,"text":"And what they've done\nis rigged the desks to the ceiling."},{"time":359445,"text":"And at 6pm every day,"},{"time":360621,"text":"it doesn't matter who you're emailing\nor what you're doing,"},{"time":363452,"text":"the desks rise to the ceiling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364953,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":366085,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":367359,"text":"Four days a week, the space\nturns into a yoga studio,"},{"time":371626,"text":"one day a week, into a dance club."},{"time":373281,"text":"It's really up to you which ones\nyou stick around for."},{"time":375834,"text":"But this is a great stopping rule,"},{"time":377545,"text":"because it means at the end of the day,"},{"time":379456,"text":"everything stops, there's no way to work."},{"time":381517,"text":"At Daimler, the German car company,\nthey've got another great strategy."},{"time":384985,"text":"When you go on vacation,"},{"time":386539,"text":"instead of saying,\n\"This person's on vacation,"},{"time":388767,"text":"they'll get back to you eventually,\""},{"time":390514,"text":"they say, \"This person's on vacation,\nso we've deleted your email."},{"time":393760,"text":"This person will never see\nthe email you just sent.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":396430,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":397470,"text":"\"You can email back in a couple of weeks,"},{"time":400135,"text":"or you can email someone else.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":401645,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":402697,"text":"And so --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":403893,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408882,"text":"You can imagine what that's like."},{"time":410544,"text":"You go on vacation,\nand you're actually on vacation."},{"time":413026,"text":"The people who work at this company feel"},{"time":415019,"text":"that they actually get a break from work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417405,"text":"But of course, that doesn't tell us much"},{"time":419346,"text":"about what we should do\nat home in our own lives,"},{"time":421669,"text":"so I want to make some suggestions."},{"time":423375,"text":"It's easy to say, between 5 and 6pm,\nI'm going to not use my phone."},{"time":427892,"text":"The problem is, 5 and 6pm\nlooks different on different days."},{"time":431347,"text":"I think a far better strategy is to say,"},{"time":433558,"text":"I do certain things every day,"},{"time":435051,"text":"there are certain occasions\nthat happen every day,"},{"time":437429,"text":"like eating dinner."},{"time":438712,"text":"Sometimes I'll be alone,"},{"time":440054,"text":"sometimes with other people,"},{"time":441584,"text":"sometimes in a restaurant,"},{"time":442887,"text":"sometimes at home,"},{"time":444099,"text":"but the rule that I've adopted is:\nI will never use my phone at the table."},{"time":448123,"text":"It's far away,"},{"time":449581,"text":"as far away as possible."},{"time":451066,"text":"Because we're really bad\nat resisting temptation."},{"time":453399,"text":"But when you have a stopping cue\nthat, every time dinner begins,"},{"time":456494,"text":"my phone goes far away,"},{"time":457674,"text":"you avoid temptation all together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459366,"text":"At first, it hurts."},{"time":461107,"text":"I had massive FOMO."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462753,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463843,"text":"I struggled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465369,"text":"But what happens is, you get used to it."},{"time":467323,"text":"You overcome the withdrawal\nthe same way you would from a drug,"},{"time":470445,"text":"and what happens is, life becomes\nmore colorful, richer,"},{"time":473254,"text":"more interesting --"},{"time":474433,"text":"you have better conversations."},{"time":476107,"text":"You really connect with the people\nwho are there with you."},{"time":479155,"text":"I think it's a fantastic strategy,"},{"time":480823,"text":"and we know it works,\nbecause when people do this --"},{"time":483336,"text":"and I've tracked a lot of people\nwho have tried this --"},{"time":485950,"text":"it expands."},{"time":487144,"text":"They feel so good about it,"},{"time":488484,"text":"they start doing it for the first\nhour of the day in the morning."},{"time":491600,"text":"They start putting their phones\non airplane mode on the weekend."},{"time":494749,"text":"That way, your phone remains a camera,\nbut it's no longer a phone."},{"time":498510,"text":"It's a really powerful idea,"},{"time":499869,"text":"and we know people feel much better\nabout their lives when they do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503973,"text":"So what's the take home here?"},{"time":505586,"text":"Screens are miraculous;\nI've already said that,"},{"time":507849,"text":"and I feel that it's true."},{"time":509225,"text":"But the way we use them is a lot like\ndriving down a really fast, long road,"},{"time":513869,"text":"and you're in a car where the accelerator\nis mashed to the floor,"},{"time":517056,"text":"it's kind of hard\nto reach the brake pedal."},{"time":519128,"text":"You've got a choice."},{"time":521510,"text":"You can either glide by, past,\nsay, the beautiful ocean scenes"},{"time":525697,"text":"and take snaps out the window --\nthat's the easy thing to do --"},{"time":528817,"text":"or you can go out of your way\nto move the car to the side of the road,"},{"time":532381,"text":"to push that brake pedal,"},{"time":533877,"text":"to get out,"},{"time":535054,"text":"take off your shoes and socks,"},{"time":536959,"text":"take a couple of steps onto the sand,"},{"time":539248,"text":"feel what the sand feels like\nunder your feet,"},{"time":541512,"text":"walk to the ocean,"},{"time":542687,"text":"and let the ocean lap at your ankles."},{"time":545207,"text":"Your life will be richer\nand more meaningful"},{"time":548046,"text":"because you breathe in that experience,"},{"time":550288,"text":"and because you've left\nyour phone in the car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552708,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553903,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}